import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='goals', bins=20, kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of goals scored by teams in the league?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    cards_data = data[['player_name', 'yellow_cards', 'red_cards']]
    cards_data = cards_data.groupby('player_name').sum().reset_index()
    cards_data = cards_data.sort_values(by=['yellow_cards', 'red_cards'], ascending=False)
    
    sns.barplot(x='player_name', y='yellow_cards', data=cards_data, color='yellow', label='Yellow Cards')
    sns.barplot(x='player_name', y='red_cards', data=cards_data, color='red', label='Red Cards', bottom=cards_data['yellow_cards'])
    
    plt.xlabel('Player Name')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Cards')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yellow and red cards given to players in the league?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=90)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    home_away_wins = data.groupby(['home_team', 'away_team']).size().unstack()
    home_away_wins.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home and away wins in the league?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
